This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel algorithm for domain adaptation based on deep neural networks. The paper also involves image classification tasks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the inter-class semantic relationships, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves benchmark datasets, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
